COMPARATOR

- An interface
- A logical comparison of instances
- Used implicitly by sort method of Array and Collections utility classes.

method call						fact								result
instance2.compare(instance1)	instance2 is greater than d1		1
instance2.compare(instance1)	instance2 and instance1 are same	0
instance2.compare(instance1)	instance2 is smaller than instance1	-1	

- Let's write a custom Employee class called as MyEmployee.
- This class will store salary, age and entrance date of the employee.
- We want to sort the employees by their salary, age or entrance date.
- That's why we will write SalaryComparatpr, AgeComparator and EntranceDateComparator
